State v. Samuel Alpert.

May Term, 1913.

Present: Rowell, C. J., Munson, Watson, Haselton, and Powers, JJ. Opinion filed October 13, 1913. Complaint for knowingly receiving and concealing stolen goods, filed at a special term of Chittenden County Court begun *163on December 16, 1912. The same proceedings were had below in this case as in State v. Alfred, the report of which immediately precedes this. V. A. Bullard and M. G. Leary for the respondent. Theodore E. Hopkins, State’s Attorney, and Henry B. Shaiv for the State. "Watson, J.

The questions presented in this case are not different from those determined in State of Vermont v. Louis Alfred, (ante, p. 157), and the holdings there made are controlling here.

Judgment that there was no error in the proceedings, and that the respondent take nothing by his exceptions. Let execution be done.
